  "text": "Sensitivity of AD profitability to changes in the price for electricity sold back to the grid and available grant support were included. Values for the price of electricity as well as the percentage of capital costs covered by grant support were modeled after programs in other U.S. states. Motivated by Vermont's feed-in-tariff and incentive rate of $0.20/kWh [CITATION_1] , sensitivity analysis was conducted assuming excess energy sales to the grid priced at $0.05/kWh, $0.10/kWh, $.15/kWh, and $0.20/kWh. Further, as shown in [CITATION_2] , based on responses from producers grant support up to 75% of initial capital costs greatly increases NPV of projects. Thus, for this sensitivity analysis, grant support of 25%, 50%, and 75% of initial capital costs was included. Under the most favorable conditions, AD installation would occur with high electricity prices and considerable grant support. Thus, one analysis was conducted assuming grant support of 75% of initial capital costs and excess electricity sales priced at $0.20/kWh.",
